remarks.para:
The meaning of the width parameter depends on the data series type:


Line - width of the line;

Dots - size of dots (rectangular dots with specified width and the same height);

Connected dots - size of dots (dots are connected with one pixel width line).

example.code:
// create [1, 10] range
var range1 = new IntRange(1, 10);

// create [5, 15] range
var range2 = new IntRange(5, 15);

check if values is inside of the first range
if (range1.IsInside(7))
{
    // ...
}

// check if the second range is inside of the first range
if (range1.IsInside(range2))
{
    // ...
}

// check if two ranges overlap
if (range1.IsOverlapping(range2))
{
    // ...
}
